# 智慧桥 WisdomBridge — Harness Engineering Rules
# 本文件为全局工程护栏，每次对话自动注入。
# 细节规范见 .cursor/rules/*.mdc（按 glob 自动触发）。

# ============================================================
# 1. ARCHITECTURE — Layer Dependency DAG
# ============================================================
#
#   L0  shared/schema.ts          零依赖；Drizzle 表定义 + Zod schema + TS 类型
#        ^
#   L1  server/storage.ts         仅依赖 L0（@shared/schema）+ drizzle-orm
#        ^
#   L2  server/routes.ts          依赖 L0 + L1（./storage）+ Express / 第三方库
#        ^
#   L3  client/src/**             通过 HTTP 调用 L2；可 import L0 的类型（type-only）
#
# IMPORT RULES (violations = immediate revert):
#
#   shared/           MUST NOT import from server/ or client/
#   server/storage.ts MUST only import from @shared/schema, drizzle-orm, better-sqlite3
#   server/routes.ts  MUST only import from ./storage, @shared/schema, express, third-party libs
#   client/           MUST NOT import from server/ — communicate via apiRequest() only
#   client/src/components/ui/*  FROZEN — never modify shadcn base components
#   server/index.ts             FROZEN — never modify server bootstrap
#   server/vite.ts              FROZEN — never modify Vite middleware

# ============================================================
# 2. CODING STANDARDS
# ============================================================

## TypeScript
- strict mode enabled; avoid `any` in new code
- Use path aliases: `@/` → client/src/, `@shared/` → shared/
- Export types with `export type` when no runtime value is needed

## React (client/)
- Function components with named default export: `export default function PageName()`
- Data fetching: useQuery({ queryKey: ["/api/..."] }) for reads
- Data mutation: useMutation + apiRequest("METHOD", "/api/...", body)
- After mutation success: queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: [...] })
- NEVER use raw fetch() in business code — always go through apiRequest()
- NEVER use localStorage / sessionStorage / indexedDB
- Auth: useAuth() hook — user / login / logout
- Routing: wouter hash mode (useHashLocation); register all routes in App.tsx
- Protected pages wrapped in <ProtectedLayout>
- Forms: react-hook-form + zodResolver + drizzle-zod insert schema
- Every interactive element MUST have a data-testid attribute

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS v3, utility-first
- Colors via CSS variables (bg-primary, text-muted-foreground, etc.) — no hardcoded hex
- Responsive: mobile-first, md: breakpoint (768px) for desktop
- wouter <Link> renders <a> — NEVER nest another <a> inside it

## Express (server/)
- Thin routes: validate params → call storage method → return result
- Auth middleware: requireAuth (logged in), requireAdmin (admin role)
- Response format: success → JSON object; error → { message: "..." } + HTTP status
- All DB operations go through the storage object (IStorage interface)
- Drizzle queries are synchronous: .get() for single row, .all() for multiple
- Write operations: .returning().get() to get the inserted/updated record

## Database (shared/ + server/storage.ts)
- Tables defined in shared/schema.ts using sqliteTable()
- Each table exports: table, insertSchema (drizzle-zod), InsertType, SelectType
- SQLite has no array columns — use JSON text + JSON.parse() in application layer
- Schema change procedure:
    1. Modify shared/schema.ts
    2. Update CREATE TABLE SQL in server/storage.ts
    3. Update IStorage interface + DatabaseStorage implementation
    4. Delete data.db → restart server
    5. Update related API routes and frontend pages

## UI Copy
- ALL user-facing text MUST be in Chinese (简体中文)
- Variable names, comments, and code in English

# ============================================================
# 3. PRE-EDIT DOCUMENT CHECKLIST
# ============================================================
# Before modifying code, the agent MUST read the relevant files below.
#
# ┌─────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │ When you touch...           │ First read these files                           │
# ├─────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
# │ shared/schema.ts            │ server/storage.ts (CREATE TABLE + IStorage)      │
# │ server/storage.ts           │ shared/schema.ts (table definitions)             │
# │ server/routes.ts            │ server/storage.ts (IStorage interface methods)   │
# │ New frontend page           │ client/src/App.tsx (route registration)          │
# │                             │ client/src/components/Layout.tsx (nav arrays)    │
# │ Auth logic                  │ client/src/hooks/use-auth.ts                     │
# │                             │ server/routes.ts (requireAuth / requireAdmin)    │
# │ Database / Drizzle config   │ shared/schema.ts + drizzle.config.ts             │
# │ Any file                    │ This .cursorrules (auto-injected)                │
# └─────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

# ============================================================
# 4. VERIFICATION COMMANDS
# ============================================================
# After EVERY code change, the agent MUST run these checks before
# claiming the work is complete.
#
# Step 1 — Type check (catches compile errors across all layers):
#   npx tsc --noEmit
#
# Step 2 — Lint modified files (catches style / logic issues):
#   Use the ReadLints tool on every file you edited
#
# Step 3 — Manual checklist (agent self-review):
#   [ ] All new UI text is in Chinese
#   [ ] Every new interactive element has data-testid
#   [ ] No import violates the Layer Dependency DAG (Section 1)
#   [ ] No raw fetch() added outside queryClient.ts
#   [ ] No modification to FROZEN files (ui/*, index.ts, vite.ts)
#   [ ] If schema changed: storage.ts CREATE TABLE updated, data.db deleted
#   [ ] If new page: route added in App.tsx, nav item in Layout.tsx (if needed)
#
# Step 4 — If user requests, commit with conventional format:
#   git add -A
#   git commit -m "type: 简短中文描述"
#   Types: feat / fix / refactor / chore / docs

# ============================================================
# 5. RELATIONSHIP WITH .cursor/rules/*.mdc
# ============================================================
# This .cursorrules = global guardrails (always active).
# .cursor/rules/*.mdc  = layer-specific details (activated by glob match).
#
#   01-project-global.mdc  — Project intro, tech stack, iron rules
#   02-frontend.mdc        — React / wouter / TanStack Query / Tailwind details
#   03-backend.mdc         — Express / storage / session details
#   04-database.mdc        — Drizzle / SQLite / schema change workflow
#   05-workflow.mdc        — Plan → Work → Review → Ship loop
#   06-new-feature.mdc     — New feature checklist (data → API → UI → nav)
#   07-bugfix.mdc          — Bug diagnosis & common failure modes
#
# Do NOT duplicate .mdc content here. This file focuses on:
#   - Architectural boundaries (what can import what)
#   - Cross-cutting verification steps
#   - Pre-edit reading requirements
